======================
gedit 2.3.1 - "Colors"
======================

This is the first version of gedit supporting syntax highlighting.

Starting from this release gedit depends on GtkSourceView.
I'd like to thank Gustavo and Jeroen that greatly helped me in re-factoring
GtkSourceView


Enhancements
============

- Syntax highlighting (Paolo Maggi)
- New help files for for de es fr it sv ja ko zh_CN zh_TW (Mike Lei)
- New viewer control for nautilus with syntax highlighting (Jeroen Zwartepoorte)


Fixes
=====

- Bug #105563 - gedit (2.2.0.1) fail to compile with new Aspell/Pspell 0.50.3 (Paolo)
- Bug #106129 - Package should use the AM_GCONF_SOURCE_2 macro (Julio Merino)
- Set accelerator for the Go to Line verb (Paolo)
- Find Next is now grayed out if no previous find action has been performed (Paolo) 
- The toolbar will not grab the focus when a button is pressed (Paolo)
- Bug #108708 - Automatic spell checker highlights unknown words already
  ignored in manual spell check (Paolo)


New and updated translations
============================

- Irish (Paul Duffy)
- Czech (Miloslav Trmac)
- Serbian (Danilo Šegan)



======================================
gedit 2.3.0 - "Weren't you listening?"
======================================

This is the first development snapshot of the 2.4 series.

- Install header files which make it possible to build plugins externally (Me)
- Split many of the plugins into a separate package, gedit-plugins (Me)
- Nifty new docs from Sun (Breda McColgan)
- Updated translations

